FBIS4-7071 "dreas080_d_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 South Korea Spokesman Welcomes New Japanese Prime Minister Spokesman Welcomes New Japanese Prime Minister OW2504080794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0752 GMT 25 Apr 94 OW2504080794 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Seoul, April 25 KYODO -- South Korea Monday [25 April] welcomed the election of Tsutomu Hata as Japan's new prime minister and expressed hope that friendly bilateral relations will further develop. Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho said the South Korean Government expects ties with Japan to reach a new level based on common ideas and values. "We are also grateful to the government of former Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa for the efforts it made for the development of Seoul-Tokyo relations," the spokesman added.
